headline: Chipotle’s (NYSE:CMG) Q4 CY2025 Sales Beat Estimates
summary: Mexican fast-food chain Chipotle (NYSE:CMG) reported Q4 CY2025 results topping the market’s revenue expectations, with sales up 4.9% year on year to $2.98 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.25 per share was 4.9% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Chipotle Q4 earnings: Stock falls on weak comp sales outlook
summary: Chipotle (CMG) reported fourth quarter earnings results that narrowly beat analyst estimates. Adjusted earnings per share (EPS) came in at $0.25 (compared to estimates of $0.24), while revenue came in at $2.98 billion (compared to estimates of $2.96 billion). Comparable sales came in at -2.5% (compared to estimates of -2.94%). Chipotle projects 2026 comparable sales at 0%, falling short of Wall Street's estimate of 1.84%. Market Domination Overtime host Josh Lipton takes a closer look at the numbers. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.

headline: Chipotle Revamps Menu And Leadership As Chicken Al Pastor Returns
summary: Chipotle Mexican Grill (NYSE:CMG) is bringing back its Chicken al Pastor menu item as part of an accelerated 2026 menu schedule. The company is pairing this product move with an executive change that combines legal and HR under one leader. Chipotle cites internal data linking limited time items like Chicken al Pastor to stronger customer engagement.
